# Windsurf IDE Rules - SafeHarbor Behavioral Health

Working on SafeHarbor Behavioral Health website (Next.js 14 + TypeScript).

## Start Session - Read Memory Bank

ALWAYS read these first:
1. `memory-bank/projectbrief.md`
2. `memory-bank/techContext.md`
3. `memory-bank/activeContext.md`
4. `memory-bank/progress.md`

This takes 2 minutes and ensures context.

## End Session - Update Memory Bank

Before ending:
1. Update `memory-bank/activeContext.md` with work summary, files changed, next steps
2. Update `memory-bank/progress.md` with completed tasks marked [x]
3. Tell user: "Memory bank updated."

## Critical Rules

1. NEVER modify `src/data/locations.ts` (15 production locations)
2. Medicaid/SoonerCare MUST be prominent
3. 988 hotline MUST be visible on all pages
4. Mobile-first design priority
5. Keep changes simple and minimal

## Commands

### "update memory bank"
→ Update activeContext.md + progress.md, confirm

### "continue where I left off"
→ Load memory bank, summarize state, ask next priority

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS (teal-500, navy-800, cream)
- Framer Motion (animations)
- Google Generative AI (Voice Agent)

## Color System

- Teal-500: #14b8a6 (primary)
- Navy-800: #1e293b (dark text)
- Cream-50: #fffbf0 (background)
- Red-600: Emergency only

## Development

```bash
npm run dev      # Port 3000
npm run build    # Production build
npm run lint     # Linting
```

## File Structure

- `src/app/[route]/page.tsx` - Pages
- `src/components/[cat]/Component.tsx` - Components
- `src/data/[name].ts` - Data files
- `memory-bank/` - Session context (read/update every session)

## Project Context

- **Goal:** Rank #1 for "child therapy Tulsa"
- **Audience:** Low-income families seeking Medicaid therapy
- **Status:** 75% launch ready
- **Key Program:** Body & Brain movement therapy

## Key Principle

Make every change as simple as possible. Impact minimal code.

